<a name="skipmaincontent"></a><h1 class="bac">LaSalle Global Trust Services Intern Program <span style="font-size: 0.6em; position: relative; top: -0.6em;">TM</span></span></h1>
<h2 class="bac">Our Business</h2>
<p class="bac">
LaSalle Global Trust Services provides securitization trust and fund administration services to the capital markets through 1,200 associates working in the U.S., Europe and Mexico.  LaSalle Global Trust Services is a market leader in the industry, and since it began 15 years ago, has served as trustee, agent and custodian on approximately $2.1 trillion in assets and has been appointed on more than 4,600 securitization transactions.  LaSalle Global Trust Services is a subsidiary of Bank of America and is part of the Chief Financial Officer group.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Program Overview</h2>
<p class="bac">
The LaSalle Global Trust Services Associates Internship is a summer development program that prepares associates for a career in the securitization and alternative fund services industry. Associates acquire essential financial and professional skills during an assignment in one of the following LaSalle Global Trust Services areas: Residential Mortgage-Backed Securities, Commercial Mortgage-Backed Securities, Collateralized Debt Obligations, Alternative Funds, Global Escrow, or Business Support.    
</p>
<p class="bac">
As a LaSalle Global Trust Services Intern Associate, you will have roles that:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Develop your knowledge of the capital markets and involved parties - investment banks, asset managers and rating agencies </li>
	<li>Require both teamwork and individual initiative to meet daily deliverables and project milestones</li>
	<li>Use financial systems to setup, monitor and analyze cash and assets holdings, trade settlement and investor reports</li>
	<li>Contribute to the research and execution of assigned business projects</li>
	<li>Participate in professional development activities and networking events </li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
The internship is designed for undergraduate students who qualify and are interested in pursing full-time employment with LaSalle Global Trust Services upon graduation.   The internship focuses on developing the following professional skills required for full-time employment opportunities in LaSalle Global Trust Services: 
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Spreadsheet and data management skills</li>
	<li>Analytical and problem-solving skills</li>
	<li>Effective time management and prioritization skills</li>
	<li>Interpersonal communication and networking skills</li>
</ul>
<p class="bac">
Interns will create a performance plan at the beginning of the summer that outlines responsibilities and professional development action plans.  Performance appraisals are provided twice during the internship: at the mid-point and at the end.  At the completion of the internship, eligible interns may be given the opportunity to interview for the LaSalle Global Trust Services Associates Program - a one year rotational development program for college graduates interested in a career in the capital markets services industry. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications</h2>
<p class="bac">
We hire an elite group of associates who are pursuing undergraduate degrees in Finance, Economics, Accounting, Engineering or Math with a minimum of a 3.0/4.0 grade point average.  Strong academics, analytical and technical skills should be accompanied by proficiencies in critical thinking, leadership, business acumen and collaboration.  Candidates must be able to work both in teams and independently, with effective time management, communication and business writing skills.  Candidates must also be client focused, proactive and demonstrate composure when challenging business situations arise.   Basic accounting coursework and MS Excel experience is recommended.</p>

